e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.0dff3839-e703-4bbd-b852-c4973ce22323.prompt=Input an XML with the content to be updated\: e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.1719a942-e3b5-40c8-a411-f85fbc7489ff.prompt=Input the resource URI to be used\: e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.1e853eb4-d307-480f-b782-48256ea66f18.description=
	Calls the Delete method of a WS-Management compliant web service, method used to delete a single resource instance. The pairs selector name and value should uniquely identify a resource, otherwise the operation will fail. 
 
Inputs\: 
webServiceURL  	- The URL of the web service where the  request message will be sent. Example\: http\://localhost\:8080/myservice/, http\://192.168.1.2\:5985/wsman/ .
resourceURI  	- The resource URI used to identify the type of resource that will be retrieved. This is usually provided in the web service WSDL. Example\: urn\:resources.wiseman.dev.java.net/traffic/1/light or http\://schemas.microsoft.com/wbem/wsman/1/wmi/root/cimv2/Win32_Service.
username 		- The username used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
password 		- The password used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
selectorNames 	- A list of properties of the requested resource, separated by delimiter, used to uniquely identify the resource. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\: id,name,color.
selectorValues	- A list of values for the properties specified in the selectorNames list, separated by delimiter. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\:2742,john doe,black.
delimiter		- Delimiter used to separate values in the selectorNames and selectorValues lists. Default value is , . Do not choose a delimiter present in the list items, otherwise the lists will not be split according to your expectation.

Responses\:
success -	The delete operation was called successfully and the returned result did not contain a fault. 
failure - 	The web service method could not be called or returned an error.

Returns\:
returnResult - A success message if the resource has been successfully deleted or an error message if the operation failed.

Note\:
	Usually when given access to a web service you will receive a web service WSDL which contains details about the web service . In the WSDL you will find the webServiceURL and resourceURI. For example, in the following WSDL fragment  the "wsa\:Address" tag specifies the webServiceURL and the "wsman\:ResourceURI" tag the resourceURI\:

	http\://localhost\:8080/myservice/
	
		urn\:resources.wiseman.dev.java.net/traffic/1/light

username 		- The username used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
password 		- The password used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
selectorNames 	- A list of properties of the requested resource, separated by delimiter, used to uniquely identify the resource. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\: id,name,color.
selectorValues	- A list of values for the properties specified in the selectorNames list, separated by delimiter. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\:2742,john doe,black.
delimiter		- Delimiter used to separate values in the selectorNames and selectorValues lists. Default value is , . Do not choose a delimiter present in the list items, otherwise the lists will not be split according to your expectation.

success -	The get operation was called successfully and the returned result did not contain a fault. 
failure - 	The web service method could not be called or returned an error.

Returns\:

	Calls the Put method of a WS-Management compliant web service, method used to update properties of a single resource instance. The pairs selector name and value should uniquely identify a resource, otherwise the operation will fail.
 
Inputs\: 
webServiceURL  	- The URL of the web service where the  request message will be sent. Example\: http\://localhost\:8080/myservice/, http\://192.168.1.2\:5985/wsman/ .
resourceURI  	- The resource URI used to identify the type of resource that will be retrieved. This is usually provided in the web service WSDL. Example\: urn\:resources.wiseman.dev.java.net/traffic/1/light or http\://schemas.microsoft.com/wbem/wsman/1/wmi/root/cimv2/Win32_Service.
username 		- The username used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
password 		- The password used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
selectorNames 	- A list of properties of the requested resource, separated by delimiter, used to uniquely identify the resource. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\: id,name,color.
selectorValues 	- A list of values for the properties specified in the selectorNames list, separated by delimiter. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\:2742,john doe,black.
delimiter		- Delimiter used to separate values in the selectorNames and selectorValues lists. Default value is , . Do not choose a delimiter present in the list items, otherwise the lists will not be split according to your expectation.
resourceContent	- The content of the resource that will be updated, in XML format. The XML should not include encoding or xml version information, but must include a namespace reference. The structure of the XML should be according to the resource XML Schema supplied by the web service provider or the request message format specified in the web service WSDL. You should clarify with the web service provider which resource properties can be changed and which are read-only, and how the service responds in case you try to update a read-only property. 
	Example\: 		
		red
		100
	               

Responses\:
success -	The put operation was called successfully and the returned result did not contain a fault.
failure - 	The web service method could not be called or returned an error.

Returns\:
returnResult - The new content of the updated  resource, in XML format, according to the resource XML Schema supplied by the web service provider.  If the operation fails this result will contain the exception message.

Note\:
	Usually when given access to a web service you will receive a web service WSDL which contains details about the web service . In the WSDL you will find the webServiceURL and resourceURI. 	Calls the Create method of a WS-Management compliant web service. The method is used to create a single resource instance using the values specified in the operation inputs. 
 
Inputs\: 
webServiceURL  	- The URL of the web service where the  request message will be sent. Example\: http\://localhost\:8080/myservice/, http\://192.168.1.2\:5985/wsman/ .
resourceURI  	- The resource URI used to identify the type of resource that will be created. This is usually provided in the web service WSDL. Example\: urn\:resources.wiseman.dev.java.net/traffic/1/light or http\://schemas.microsoft.com/wbem/wsman/1/wmi/root/cimv2/Win32_Service.
username  		- The username used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
password  		- The password used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
resourceContent 	- The content of the resource that will be created, in XML format. The XML should not include encoding or xml version information, but must include a namespace reference. The structure of the XML should be according to the resource XML Schema supplied by the web service provider or the request message format specified in the web service WSDL. 
	Example\: 
		OOLight
		bright red
		100
		100
	               
selectorNames 	- A list of properties of the requested resource, separated by delimiter, used to uniquely identify the type of resource that will be created. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\: id,name,color.
selectorValues	- A list of values for the properties specified in the selectorNames list, separated by delimiter. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\:2742,john doe,black.
delimiter		- Delimiter used to separate values in the selectorNames and selectorValues lists. Default value is , . Do not choose a delimiter present in the list items, otherwise the lists will not be split according to your expectation.

Responses\:
success -	The create operation was called successfully and the returned result did not contain a fault. Depending on the web service implementation the service method could be called successfully, the return message contain no fault but the resource not be available. This depends on the actual service implementation and you should clarify this aspect with the web service provider. 
failure - 	The web service method could not be called or returned an error.

Returns\:
returnResult - The response of the operation call, in XML format. Usually this contains details about the newly created resource (resourceURI, selector set, attributes) but it's actual format depends on the web service implementation.  If the operation fails this result will contain the exception message.

e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.c9c3762c-2408-4b59-9262-a963e3978634.prompt=Input the list of property names used to select the resource\: e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.cc3e1169-813c-470c-a3a2-b492e392abe2.prompt=Input an XML with the content of the resource to be created\: e61b6fc6-8993-40ae-9c0f-f1ba0b583000.description=
	The sample flow demostrates the usage of the operations in the WS-Transfer folder. This flow creates a resource, obtains its XML representation, updates some attributes of the resource, obtains the new XML representation of the resource and then deletes it. 
 
Inputs\: 
webServiceURL  	- The URL of the web service where the  request message will be sent. Example\: http\://localhost\:8080/myservice/, http\://192.168.1.2\:5985/wsman/ .
resourceURI  	- The resource URI used to identify the type of resource that will be retrieved. This is usually provided in the web service WSDL. Example\: urn\:resources.wiseman.dev.java.net/traffic/1/light or http\://schemas.microsoft.com/wbem/wsman/1/wmi/root/cimv2/Win32_Service.
username  		- The username used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
password  		- The password used to authenticate to the web service. If necessary, this should be supplied by the web service provider.
selectorNames 	- A list of properties of the requested resource, separated by delimiter, used to uniquely identify the resource. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\: id,name,color.
selectorValues	- A list of values for the properties specified in the selectorNames list, separated by delimiter. The existing whitespaces from the input value will not be skipped. Example\:2742,john doe,black.
delimiter		- Delimiter used to separate values in the selectorNames and selectorValues lists. Default value is , . Do not choose a delimiter present in the list items, otherwise the lists will not be split according to your expectation.
resourceContent 	- The content of the resource that will be CREATED, in XML format. The XML should not include encoding or xml version information, but must include a namespace reference. The structure of the XML should be according to the resource XML Schema supplied by the web service provider or the request format specified in the web service WSDL. 
newresourceContent 	- The content of the resource that will be UPDATED, in XML format. The XML should not include encoding or xml version information, but must include a namespace reference. The structure of the XML should be according to the resource XML Schema supplied by the web service provider or the request format specified in the web service WSDL. 

Responses\:
success -	All the operations executed with success.
failure - 	One of the operations failed.

Inputs example\:
    The following inputs allow you to run the flow and create a http listener on a computer that has WinRM installed. It then updates the attributes of the listener, and finally deletes it. Look at the returnResult of the Get steps in order to see the state of the resource before and after the update.

webServiceURL	- http\://192.168.1.1\:5985/wsman/ - Replace the IP and port with the values corresponding to you host.
resourceURI		- http\://schemas.microsoft.com/wbem/wsman/1/config/Listener - 
username		- User - Replace with a user that can connect to the given host.
password		- Password - Replace with the password corresponding to the given user.
selectorNames 	- Address,Transport - The selectors for the type of resource "Listener". 
selectorValues 	- 196.168.1.2,HTTP - Values with which the resource will be created in the first step, and then uniquelly identified in the future steps.
delimiter 		- , 
resourceContent 	- Values with which the resource will be initialized at creation.
	
		5988
		true
	
newResourceContent 	- These values will be changed in the resource configurate in the Put step of the flow.
	
		5999
		false
